physical_examinations.relevant_findings: General: AA&O x 3, NAD, calm, cooperative. HEENT: (-)LAD, mucous membranes moist, trachea midline, EOMI, PERRL. CHEST: Clear to auscultation bilaterally, (-) cyanosis. ABDOMEN: (+/-) BS x 4 quadrants, soft, mildly tender to palpation incisionally, non-distended. Incisions: clean, dry and intact, dressed and closed with steristrips. EXTREMITIES: Warm, well perfused, pulses palpable, (+/-) edema.
